    {
      "id": "80f9d2df_45a96a1b",
      "file_path": "src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/pmmapper/ssl/SSLContextFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": null,
      "message": "In many places in this class exceptions are caught and only logged. This leads in multiple places to variables being instantiated to null and/or things not set up the way they are meant to be. Is this really by intention? If null is returned there might be null pointer exceptions that are hard to troubleshoot. And there might be behaviour that is hard to understand if things haven't been properly set up. Isn't it better to rethrow/throw new exceptions when there is a failure so that it is clear that something has gone wrong?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3763,
        "name": "Henrik Andersson",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "henrik.b.andersson@est.tech",
        "username": "elinuxhenrik"
      },
      "updated": "2019-04-03 08:57:02.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "fbcf3508_c89c0483",
      "file_path": "src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/pmmapper/utils/RequestSender.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 87,
      "message": "A good practice is to compare with the string instead of the value, \"https\".equalsIgnoreCase(url.getProtocol()). This way there will not be a NullPointerException in case the value is null.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3763,
        "name": "Henrik Andersson",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "henrik.b.andersson@est.tech",
        "username": "elinuxhenrik"
      },
      "updated": "2019-04-03 08:57:02.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "f2b8ff37_4243f5a0",
      "file_path": "src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/pmmapper/utils/RequestSender.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 91,
      "message": "Since the exception here is only logged, will not the connection be improperly set up? Why not rethrow/throw other exception to show that things are not correct?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3763,
        "name": "Henrik Andersson",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "henrik.b.andersson@est.tech",
        "username": "elinuxhenrik"
      },
      "updated": "2019-04-03 08:57:02.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "c36d3f55_bc0cacca",
      "file_path": "src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/pmmapper/utils/RequestSender.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 113,
      "message": "There will be a Sonar warning if a generic exception is used instead of a dedicated one. So best to create/use a dedicated exception here.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3763,
        "name": "Henrik Andersson",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "henrik.b.andersson@est.tech",
        "username": "elinuxhenrik"
      },
      "updated": "2019-04-03 08:57:02.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
